-- Japan, Vietnam to Agree to Jointly Develop Rare-Earth Deposits, Nikke Says
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-10-21T17:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/japan-vietnam-to-agree-to-jointly-develop-rare-earth-deposits-nikke-says.html
Japan will work with Vietnam to tap
rare-earth metal deposits in the Southeast Asian country, with
Japan Prime Minister Naoto Kan and Vietnam counterpart Nguyen
Tan Dung to agree on cooperation in a meeting on Oct. 24, Nikkei
English News said.  Companies including Sumitomo Corp., Toyota Tsusho Corp. and
Sojitz Corp. are preparing to develop mines in Vietnam,
according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  